    "solution": "<picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kszcz04j/202f1a7f-72d4-457a-a368-5e41b1f99d5f/0c9fb240-09f6-11ec-837d-2903eea50152/file-1kszcz04k-320w.jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 500px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kszcz04j/202f1a7f-72d4-457a-a368-5e41b1f99d5f/0c9fb240-09f6-11ec-837d-2903eea50152/file-1kszcz04k-500w.jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 680px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kszcz04j/202f1a7f-72d4-457a-a368-5e41b1f99d5f/0c9fb240-09f6-11ec-837d-2903eea50152/file-1kszcz04k-680w.jpeg\"><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kszcz04j/202f1a7f-72d4-457a-a368-5e41b1f99d5f/0c9fb240-09f6-11ec-837d-2903eea50152/file-1kszcz04k.jpeg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2019 Paper 2 Offline Physics - Laws of Motion Question 16 English Explanation 1\"></picture> <br><br>In the frame of pulley B,<br><br>the hanging masses have accelerations :<br><br>$$M \\to ({a_2} - {a_1})$$<br><br>$$2M \\to ({a_3} - {a_1})$$ : downward.<br><br>$$ \\therefore $$ $$({a_2} - {a_1})$$ = $$( - {a_3} - {a_1})$$ [constant]<br><br>Assuming that the extension of the spring is x<br><br>We consider the FBD of A :<br><br>$$2M.{{{d^2}x} \\over {d{t^2}}} = 2T - kx$$<br><br> <img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kszd4ifv/1f14fe91-1d9a-4e46-9fcb-15428359e1a5/a5d112b0-09f6-11ec-ac1f-e362cac4ba2a/file-1kszd4ifw.jpeg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2019 Paper 2 Offline Physics - Laws of Motion Question 16 English Explanation 2\"> <br><br>where, $${a_1} \\equiv {{{d^2}x} \\over {d{t^2}}}$$ ....(i)<br><br>and the FBD of the rest of the system in the frame of pulley B :<br><br> <picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kszd7rg4/c943f044-1df6-41c6-9d48-32c1b41150da/0033a740-09f7-11ec-ac1f-e362cac4ba2a/file-1kszd7rg5-320w.jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 500px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kszd7rg4/c943f044-1df6-41c6-9d48-32c1b41150da/0033a740-09f7-11ec-ac1f-e362cac4ba2a/file-1kszd7rg5-500w.jpeg\"><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kszd7rg4/c943f044-1df6-41c6-9d48-32c1b41150da/0033a740-09f7-11ec-ac1f-e362cac4ba2a/file-1kszd7rg5.jpeg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2019 Paper 2 Offline Physics - Laws of Motion Question 16 English Explanation 3\"></picture> <br><br>Upward acceleration of block M w.r.t. the pulley B = Downward acceleration of block 2M w.r.t. the pulley.<br><br>$${{T - M(g - {a_1})} \\over M} = {{2M(g - {a_1}) - T} \\over {2M}}$$<br><br>$$ \\Rightarrow T = {{4M} \\over 3}(g - {a_1})$$ .....(ii)<br><br>Substituting in Eq. (i), we get<br><br>$$2M.{a_1} = {{8M} \\over 3}(g - {a_1}) - kx$$<br><br>or $${{14M} \\over 3}{a_1} = {{8Mg} \\over 3} - kx$$ ....(iii)<br><br>This is equation of SHM<br><br>Maximum extension = 2 $$ \\times $$ amplitude<br><br>i.e., $${x_0} = 2 \\times {{8Mg} \\over {3k}}$$<br><br>Amplitude = $${{{x_0}} \\over 2} = {{3Mg} \\over {3k}}$$ and $$\\omega  = \\sqrt {{{3k} \\over {14M}}} $$<br><br>At $${{{x_0}} \\over 4}$$, acceleration is easily found from Eq. (iii),<br><br>$${{14M} \\over 3}{a_1} = {{8Mg} \\over 3} - {{4Mg} \\over 3}$$<br><br>$${a_1} = {{2g} \\over 7}$$<br><br>At $${{{x_0}} \\over 2}$$, speed of the block<br><br>$$(2M) = \\omega  \\times \\,amplitude$$<br><br>= $$\\sqrt {{{3k} \\over {14M}}}  \\times {{8Mg} \\over {3k}}$$<br><br>$$ \\therefore $$ option (a) is correct.",
