    ],
    "solution": "<img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/oirDkdiHDvToTkttw/HE8BcHJazRhESLWWpXl4ozZojFsed/96u46ru4EM7AG5zgtmF78m/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"AIEEE 2007 Physics - Laws of Motion Question 137 English Explanation\">\n<br><b>From free body-diagram of $$m$$</b>\n<br><br>we get $$T = ma$$ \n<br><br><b>From free body-diagram of $$M$$</b>\n<br><br>we get $$F-T=Ma$$\n<br><br>where $$T$$ is force due to spring\n<br><br>$$ \\Rightarrow F - ma = Ma$$ \n<br><br>$$ \\Rightarrow$$ $$F=Ma+ma$$\n<br><br>$$\\therefore$$ $$a = {F \\over {M + m}}$$\n<br><br>Now, force acting on the block of mass $$m$$ is \n<br><br>$$ma = m\\left( {{F \\over {M + m}}} \\right) = {{mF} \\over {m + M}}.$$",
